<h2 id="section-top">Rheumatology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=27">Barking, Havering and Redbridge University Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent1fcba76fc2fd458b9472f0e6ef1c9198">
</div>
<p>We provide a service for a wide range of musculoskeletal diseases via outpatient clinics, infusions and injection clinics.<br/><br/>The service is run by six rheumatology consultants working across Queen's Hospital (ground floor, blue zone, outpatients team 1) and King George Hospitals(ground floor, block B) as well as Brentwood Community Hospital - all supported by nurse specialists. The service runs daily between 9am and 5pm.<br/><br/>We also run a nurse-led telephone advice line service available for questions relating to treatments, musculoskeletal complaints, rheumatological and autoimmune conditions, metabolic bone disorders, inflammatory back pain and joint injections. Patients can contact the advice line at Queen's Hospital on 01708 435 000 ext 4821 or at King George Hospital on 020 8970 8408.</p>
<p>We run regular outpatient clinics and offer a day case service for patients requiring intravenous drugs. We also offer an inpatient service when required.</p>
<p><br/>We have access to a wide range of diagnostic equipment including x-rays, DEXA Nuclear, CT and ultrasound.<br/><br/>The Rheumatology service also provides training and education, research and clinical trials including training to medical students and junior doctors and academic activity by taking part in national (CLRN) and international studies.</p>
<p>Our secretaries can be contacted on 020 8970 8311 at King George Hospital or 01708 435 000 ext 2723 or 2721 at Queen's Hospital.Â </p></div>
</div>
</div>
